wikipedia_page.main: John Moyer Heathcote (9 November 1800 – 27 March 1892) was the son of John Heathcote. He was an English first-class cricketer. He is recorded as a batsman for Cambridge University in two matches in 1820, totalling 33 runs with a highest score of 19.John Moyer Heathcote was educated at Eton College and St John's College, Cambridge. He stood for election as MP for Huntingdonshire in 1857 and was elected but his return was subsequently invalidated.
